			<ns0:name>b...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105821748722532785568/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">This is a good idea.  It's definitely more robust, and will work with most embeddings of NaCl.  The only problem with it is non-composability -- if there are other libraries used by the embedding program that also want to patch NTDLL.DLL, then chances are that we'd abort early since DLL version-detection code to ensure we're applying the patches properly will get confused by earlier patch (or vice versa).</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-11-28T22:10:54.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-11-28T22:10:54.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 2 by b...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=3175#c2" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/3175/comments/full/2" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>